# Component Architecture Rules

## Core Principles

- **One component per file** - Split complex components, use composition
- **Folder-based structure** - Each component gets its own folder with barrel export
- **Kebab-case naming** - `auth-status/`, `user-profile.tsx`
- **Co-located files** - Types, tests, utils in same folder

## Folder Structure

```
src/components/
├── component-name/
│   ├── index.ts                    ← Barrel export
│   ├── component-name.tsx          ← Main component
│   ├── component-name.types.ts     ← Component types
│   ├── component-name.test.tsx     ← Tests
│   └── sub-component/              ← Nested components (same pattern)
```

## Component Placement

- **Shared components**: `src/components/` (reusable across app)
- **Page-specific**: `src/app/page-name/` (one-off components)
- **Feature-specific**: `src/features/feature/components/` (complex domains)

## Import Patterns

```typescript
// ✅ Barrel imports
import ComponentName from "@/components/component-name";

// ❌ Direct file imports
import ComponentName from "@/components/component-name/component-name";
```

## Barrel Export Pattern

```typescript
// component-name/index.ts
export { default } from "./component-name";
export type { ComponentNameProps } from "./component-name.types";
```

## File Naming

- Folders: `kebab-case` (`auth-status/`)
- Files: `kebab-case` with purpose suffix (`auth-status.types.ts`)
- Suffixes: `.types.ts`, `.test.tsx`, `.utils.ts`, `.hooks.ts`
